rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects baseball statistics about a given player of a given team during a specific season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player on the given team has appeared at home plate during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: At Bats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player of the given team did not swing at four pitches outside of the strike zone and was awarded first base during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bases on Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has advanced to a base to which he or she is not entitled during the given season and as part of the given team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bases Stolen

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property indicating the number of times that the given player of the given team has hit at bat divided by the total number of times that the player has been at bat during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Average

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player of the given team has hit the ball while on bat and reached second base safely during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Doubles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of baseball games played by the given player of the given team during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of ground balls hit by the given player of the given team that became double plays during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ground into Double Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of home runs hit by the given player of the given team with the bases loaded during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grand Slams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player of the given team was touched by a pitch and awarded first base during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hit by Pitch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates that number of times that the given player of the given team reached base because of a batted ball without an error by the opposing team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has hit the ball while on bat and reached home base safely.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Home Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of times that the given player of the given team was awarded first base because of balls intentionally thrown at the batter by the pitcher during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Intentional Bases on Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates a complex calculation, viz. the number of times that the given player of the given team reached base (H + BB + HBP) divided by at bats plus walks plus hit by pitch plus sacrifice flies (AB + BB + HBP + SF) of the given player of the given team during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: On Base Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the player about which the batting statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of runners who made it to home base on the basis of the batting of the given player of the given team during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs Batted in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of times that the given player of the given team crossed home plate during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of fly balls which were hit by the given player of the given team during the given season to the outfield and which allowed a base runner to move forward.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacrifice Flies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of bunts which were hit by the given player of the given team during the given season and which allowed a base runner to move forward.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacrifice Hits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the season about which the batting statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the total bases achieved on hits divided by at-bats for the given player of the given team during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Slugging Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player of the given team reaches the third strike or bunts the ball foul on the third strike.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strikeouts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the baseball team about which the batting statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player of the given team has hit the ball while on bat and reached third base safely during the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Triples

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all baseball coaches. Currently this definition includes both professional and non-professional baseball coaches. Also note this set doesn't include baseball managers for professional baseball teams, which are the equivalent of head coaches in other sports and in college baseball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Coach
current_team_coaching
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.sports_team_coach.teams_coached instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.sports_team_coach.teams_coached]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of coaching positions in baseball teams. Positions in baseball include the manager (a position similar to head coach in other sports), pitching coach, and bullpen coach.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Coaching Position
Baseball Conference
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This has the same meaning as baseball.league. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:baseball.league]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The regulated organization under which the team competes.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: League
Current Coaching Tenure
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of baseball divisions. In professional American baseball, the two baseball leagues are divided into three divisions each.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Division

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The conference that the division resides in.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Conference
Historical Coaching Tenure
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.sports_team_coach_tenure]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the positions of a baseball manager, viz. the team and the time frame. Note that, despite the name, this type is used to store both current and historic managerial positions.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Historical Managerial Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies when the baseball manager position began.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: From

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the baseball manager.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Manager

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the team of the given baseball manager.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies when the baseball manager position ended.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: To

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing all groupings of baseball teams. In both professional American and Japanese baseball, there are, at the highest level, two leagues that make up the professional league of baseball. Note that this type covers conferences, divisions, and every other collection of baseball teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball league to another league which is a part of the first, e.g. a conference or a division.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball League

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a baseball league to a team that is a part of the league.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Teams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects baseball statistics about a given player during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lifetime Batting Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has appeared at home plate during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: At Bats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player did not swing at four pitches outside of the strike zone and was awarded first base during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bases on Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has advanced to a base to which he or she is not entitled during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bases Stolen

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property indicating the number of times that the given player has hit at bat divided by the total number of times that the player has been at bat during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Average

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has hit the ball while on bat and reached second base safely during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Doubles

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the season when the given player ended his career in major league baseball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ending Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of baseball games played by the given player during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of ground balls hit by the given player that became double plays during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Ground into Double Play

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of home runs hit by the given player with the bases loaded during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Grand Slams

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player was touched by a pitch and awarded first base during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hit by Pitch

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates that number of times that the given player over his entire major league career reached base because of a batted ball without an error by the opposing team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player has hit the ball while on bat and reached home base safely during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Home Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of times that the given player was awarded first base because of balls intentionally thrown at the batter by the pitcher during the player's entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Intentional Bases on Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the latest season for which statistics are provided for the given player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Last Statistics Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates how often the given player during his entire major league career reached base for any reason other than a fielding error, fielder's choice, dropped/uncaught third strike, fielder's obstruction or catcher's interference.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: On Base Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the major league baseball player about whom lifetime batting statistics are provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of runners who made it to home base on the basis of the batting of the given player during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs Batted in

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that records the number of times that the given player crossed home plate during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of fly balls which were hit by the given player during his entire major league career to the outfield and which allowed a base runner to move forward.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacrifice Flies

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of bunts which were hit by the given player during his entire major league career and which allowed a base runner to move forward.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Sacrifice Hits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the total bases achieved on hits divided by at-bats for the given player during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Slugging Percentage

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the season when the given player started his career in major league baseball.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Starting Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player reached the third strike or bunted the ball foul on the third strike during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strikeouts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that indicates the number of times that the given player hit the ball while on bat and reached third base safely during his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Triples

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all baseball managers. The manager of a baseball team is equivalent to the head coach of other North American professional sports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Manager

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a baseball manager to information about the teams that he or she managed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Former Teams Managed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Relationship collecting data on a baseball pitcher's statistics for a given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pitching Season Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of base on balls, which is the number of times pitching four balls, allowing the batter to take first base. Also known as walks.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Base on Balls

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of games in which the pitcher entered the game in a save situation and the pitcher eliminated his team's lead.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Blown Save

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of games the pitcher completed for the given season. This is the number of games in which the pitcher is the only pitcher for the team.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Complete Game

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of earned runs. These are runs that did not occur as a result of errors or passed balls for a given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Earned Run

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of times a pitcher pitched in a professional game for the season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games Pitched

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of games pitched where the pitcher was the first pitcher for the team for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Games Started

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of hits the pitcher allowed for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hits

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of holds for the pitcher for a given season. Holds are games in which the pitcher entered in a save situation, recorded at least one out, did not surrender the lead, and did not complete the game.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Holds

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of home runs the pitcher allowed for the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Home Runs

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of outs recorded while pitching for the given season divided by three.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Innings Pitched

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the attributed mso:baseball.player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of games in a given season in which the pitcher enters a game led by the pitcher's team, finishes the game without surrendering the lead, is not the winning pitcher, and either (a) the lead was three runs or fewer when the pitcher entered the game; (b) the potential tying run was on base, at bat, or on deck; or (c) the pitcher pitched three or more innings.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Saves

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the mso:sports.season for which the collected data is valid.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of shutouts the pitcher has pitched for the given season. Shutouts are the games in which the pitcher allowed no runs.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Shutout

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:baseball.pitching_season_statistics to the number of strikeouts for the pitcher for a given season. Strikeouts are when the pitcher pitches three strikes to a batter, effectively ending the batter's turn at play.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Strikeouts

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all professional baseball players.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Player

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball player to an award won by the baseball player.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Award

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball player to his or her identifier in the Baseball Almanac.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Almanac ID

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player's batting hand
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Bats

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball player to statistics about the player's performance relative to a particular team and season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Batting Statistics
current_team
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.pro_athlete.team instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[ mso:sports.pro_athlete.team]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball player to the date, if any, that the player was inducted into the Baseball Hall of Fame.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Hall Of Fame Induction

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a baseball player to statistics about the player's performance over his entire major league career.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Lifetime Batting Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball player to one of the positions held by the player in his or her major league career, e.g. outfielder or first baseman.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Player's throwing hand
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Throws

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type containing standard descriptors for roles on a baseball team, e.g. pitcher, outfielder, and first baseman.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of positions in baseball. These positions include player positions and coaching positions, like shortstops, pitcher, pitching coach, and manager.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Roster Position

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of baseball teams. This collection includes professional, minor league, college, and amateur teams.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Team
current_coaches
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:sports.team.coach instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.team.coach]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Current Manager
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use mso:baseball.team.historical_managers instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:baseball.team.historical_managers]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: current_roster
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: Use sports.team.roster instead, as this item will not be supported. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:sports.team.roster ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates a baseball team to information about the managers of the team. The manager of a baseball team is equivalent to the head coach of other North American professional sports.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Historical Managers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a baseball team to information about the number of wins and losses of the team in a given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A type that collects information about the number of wins and losses of a given baseball team in a given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Baseball Team Statistics

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of games lost by the given baseball team in the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Losses

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the season for which information about losses and wins is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Season

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that specifies the baseball team for which information about losses and wins is provided.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Team

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of games won by the given baseball team in the given season.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Wins
